            <fr:anchor>11402</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-0051</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-0051.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="An alternative definition of duploids">An alternative definition of duploids</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Observation</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Equivalently, we can define a <fr:link href="jms-0050.xml" title="Duploid" addr="jms-0050" type="local">duploid</fr:link> to be a <fr:link href="jms-004T.xml" title="Univalent deductive system" addr="jms-004T" type="local">univalent</fr:link> <fr:link href="jms-004F.xml" title="Preduploid" addr="jms-004F" type="local">preduploid</fr:link> such that every object is <fr:em>merely equipped with</fr:em> both an <fr:link href="jms-004M.xml" title="Upshift structure" addr="jms-004M" type="local">upshift</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="jms-004P.xml" title="Downshift structure" addr="jms-004P" type="local">downshift</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p>To see that the <fr:link href="jms-0050.xml" title="Duploid" addr="jms-0050" type="local">main definition</fr:link> implies our alternative definition, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be an object of the preduploid; because we are proving that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>merely equipped with</fr:em> both an <fr:link href="jms-004M.xml" title="Upshift structure" addr="jms-004M" type="local">upshift</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="jms-004P.xml" title="Downshift structure" addr="jms-004P" type="local">downshift</fr:link>, we may proceed by cases on the <fr:link href="jms-0045.xml" title="Polarized object" addr="jms-0045" type="local">polarization</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-004B.xml" title="Positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">positive</fr:link>, we choose the identity map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\vdash  A]]></fr:tex> for the downshift and we use our assumption to deduce that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> has an upshift.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-004B.xml" title="Positive and negative objects" addr="jms-004B" type="local">negative</fr:link>, we choose the identity map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\vdash  A]]></fr:tex> for the upshift and we use our assumption to deduce that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> has a downshift.</fr:li></fr:ol>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>4</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>5549</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/759</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-759.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Conversely, assume that every object is merely equipped with both an upshift and a downshift. That a positive object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> has an upshift <fr:link href="jms-004X.xml" title="Uniqueness of upshifts" addr="jms-004X" type="local">is a proposition</fr:link>, so we can use our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> <fr:em>merely</fr:em> has an upshift. That a negative object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> has a downshift <fr:link href="jms-004Z.xml" title="Uniqueness of downshifts" addr="jms-004Z" type="local">is likewise a proposition</fr:link>, so we can use our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> <fr:em>merely</fr:em> has a downshift.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
