          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> be a deductive system, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : A\vdash  B]]></fr:tex> be a morphism in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>. Then both the type of (linear, thunkable) <fr:link href="jms-004O.xml" title="Inverses in a deductive system" addr="jms-004O" type="local">inverses</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a proposition.</fr:p>
