            <fr:title text="Positive and negative objects">Positive and negative objects</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>An object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> in a <fr:link href="jms-0048.xml" title="Deductive system" addr="jms-0048" type="local">deductive system</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em>positive</fr:em> when every map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\vdash  C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-004A.xml" title="Linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">linear</fr:link>; it is called <fr:em>negative</fr:em> when every map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\vdash  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-004A.xml" title="Linear and thunkable maps" addr="jms-004A" type="local">thunkable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
