          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:C \vdash  D]]></fr:tex> be a morphism in a <fr:link href="jms-0048.xml" title="Deductive system" addr="jms-0048" type="local">deductive system</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li>We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>linear</fr:em> when for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g:B\vdash  C]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h:A\vdash  B]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h;{\mathopen {}\left (g;f\right )\mathclose {}} = {\mathopen {}\left (h;g\right )\mathclose {}};f]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>thunkable</fr:em> when for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g:D\vdash  E]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h : E\vdash  F]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f;{\mathopen {}\left (g;h\right )\mathclose {}} = {\mathopen {}\left (f;g\right )\mathclose {}};h]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2022</fr:year>
